**********************************************************************************************
•The product backlog is an inventory of all features, functions, requirements, enhancements, and 
fixes that constitute the changes to be made to the product in future releases

•Product Backlog items have the attributes of a description, order, estimate, and value
•The Development Team is responsible for all estimates, not the Product Owner or Scrum Master
•Product Backlog items often include test descriptions that will prove its completeness when "Done“
•The product backlog is a “living” document that is updated throughout the life of the project
•Product Backlog refinement is the act of adding detail, estimates, and order to items in the Product Backlog
•The Scrum Team decides how and when refinement is done
•Refinement usually consumes no more than 10% of the capacity of the Development Team
**********************************************************************************************



























